Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees.

In a #medium pot{}, combine @water{5%cups} (use a large pot and 8 cups water for 4 servings) and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low.

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @asparagus{6%ounce}; cut crosswise into 1-inch pieces. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Finely chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{3%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add @peas{4%ounce} and cook, stirring constantly, until lightly charred and tender, ~{2-4%minutes}. Remove from heat; transfer peas to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

> Pat chicken or salmon dry with paper towels; season with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in pan used for peas over medium-high heat. Add @salmon{10%ounce} (skin sides down); cook salmon until skin is crisp, ~{5-7%minutes}, then flip and cook until cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in same pan over medium heat. Add scallion whites, garlic, and @Arborio rice{3/4%cup}. Cook, stirring, until scallion whites and garlic are fragrant and rice is translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @water{1%cup} and @veggie stock concentrate{2}; stir until liquid has mostly absorbed. Repeat with remaining warm water—adding ½ cup at a time and stirring until liquid has absorbed—until rice is al dente and risotto is creamy, ~{18-20%minutes}.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need a little more or a little less liquid; try adding pinches of salt throughout the cooking process to make sure the risotto is well-seasoned at the end.

Once risotto has cooked 10 minutes, toss asparagus on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.

Roast asparagus on top rack until tender and lightly browned, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Once risotto is al dente, reduce heat to low. Stir in half the peas, half the asparagus, half the lemon zest, juice from half the lemon, and @plain water{1/4%cup} until combined.

Stir in half the scallion greens, half the parsley, half the @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}, and @butter{2%tablespoon} until combined and butter is melted. Season generously with salt and pepper.

> The risotto should be a little loose and saucy right before serving; it will thicken as it cools, so add more water if necessary.

Divide risotto between bowls. Top with remaining peas, asparagus, lemon zest, scallion greens, parsley, and Parmesan. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

Thinly slice salmon against the grain. Place salmon atop risotto.

> Salmon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.